reviewText: Enjoyed watching this combined "Best of Duck Dynasty" Show.  It's amazing what all they have accomplished with it.  Love that they are Christians.
If you ever need to laugh just pop in this DVD, you laugh till you hurt. This is one authentic,down to earth,funloving family that goes just a bit wild. You will Love every minute of it.
We've already watched it several times and will continue to do so.  LOVE DUCK DYNASTY!!  Highly Recommend.  Always funny.  Great therapy!!
Love the shows but the episode titles are not accurate on the menu.  The Quality Control needs to be better.

I am so happy happy happy that we have a good show to watch,there are not but less than a handfull to watch!!!! The Robertson family are peoples people and they show this with all of the episodes we have seen so far. I love the way Kay teaches the little ones how to cook and be a domestic housekeeper and how Phil teaches the girls and the boys to do man things. I also like the way Phil respects Kay and says sweet things to her. I know that my husband and I both have latched onto some of these things and tried their ways,that DO work. These shows can be very valuable to those who take heed to the ways of the Robertsons!! We are watching all of your shows and buying the books and DVDs,keep up the good work, we love all of you!!!!

My family loves duck dynasty!  Finally a show the whole family can watch with such good people.. The kids love Si,  My little grand daughter was leaving a restaurant with her parents.  They had been sitting there for a long time and never got waited on.  So they got up and as they were leaving my Little grand daughter WHO IS ONLY 5 said to them. THIS IS RID-ICU-LOUS JACK!  They laughed all the way home...
 It is so great to have something decent on TV to watch...  its an awesome show,  what a great family they are.  Watch it once and you will be hooked.
Great!

this two disc set contains eight episodes and some extra interviews. disc one has family funny business, ceo for a day, high tech redneck, frog in one, redneck logic, too close for comfort, leave it to beavers, and last a big duck-in call. all of these can all be seen in season one. but my favorite episode redneck logic, just do to the fact they blow up one of Phil's duck blinds, but hey they build him a new one.
disc two has all the extra interviews found on season one.
Great entertainment

this disc has seven episodes on it all from season one. two of them don't made much sense to be on there, those episodes are Sauvignon Beard and Redneck Roadtrip. they have nothing to do with being in the woods. yea the other five involve either hunting, fishing, or spending time in the woods.
Item was as described. Customer satisfied.

I ordered this for a dear friend of my family -- they do not live in the US so they are not aware of "Duck Dynasty Fever" -- I am happy to report that they loved it! I knew that this would be perfect for them because they are religious but also know how to laugh and have a fun time with those you love.  My friend reported that her husband was unable to turn it off until he had seen all of them because he was laughing so much.  I am definitely going to order them the other seasons!

Great dvd... but if you're an avid watcher of Duck Dynasty, you will have seen alot of what is on the first disc. The bonus disc contains some great material, though. Nice to have it in our dvd library for those times when we need our Duck Dynasty fix! This family is awesome!

I needed a way to catch up on all back shows.  this is a great way to see them with out all the commercials.

That's how I feel about watching the Robertson family.  What a breath of fresh air!  This family is not what, at first, they appear to be.  These folks from northern Louisiana are simple, educated, fun-loving, God-fearing, scruffy and hilarious!  Oh, and very wealthy!  They are multi-millionaires!!  The family dynamics are truly funny!  Check it out for yourselves.

If you own the seasons of Duck Dynasty, you don't need this. There is no additional material. Not to mention, the bonus footage ont his disc is the same as on season one and two discs. I love the Robertson's, but this disc is a waste of money.

The Robinson family is hysterical.  It is an enjoyable time of watching a show at a time or doing a Duck blitz.  We have Season 1 and 2 and this is a repeat but it reminded us so much why we enjoyed watching the show.

A co-worker told me about this show, so I tried one episode and ended up buying the dvd's for seasons 1 and 2. The antics of the Robertson family are a little contrived sometimes, but it's still very funny and entertaining.

I bought this DVD because my daughter's family does not have TV (by choice) and as I described the shows, they can now see the DVDs.  So we had a Duck Dynasty evening and laughed and laughed.  The toddler and 4 yr old got a kick out of watching all of us laugh.  And Daughter got to see some of the highjinks that are common with my Red Neck family in deep Mississippi.  It was all good.
